    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh wow okay, that's a pretty strong stance. but i mean, even if it's not a \"myth,\" aren't there legitimate economic concerns about the marginal tax rates people face when they start earning money? like, if you lose all your benefits the second you get a job, doesn't that create a real mathematical disincentive to work more hours?",
